postcontent:
8mm Lebel "Fusil Mle 1886 M93" Manufacture d'armes de Châtellerault (MAC) Lebel Model 1886 M93. $500.00

Beautiful Rifle and I also have the bayonet for it. The bayonet is a 4 sided Star shape that is now against Geneva convention so play nice and no stabbing, it's too hard to sew you up. The numbers do not match on the baynet and scabbard, though. The bluing is in great shape with no real visible rust, pitting, or wear. The bore is bright with nice rifling. Bolt and bolt face are in very nice condition and the stock has some great markings and character without abuse like gouges, deep scratches, or cracks. This would make a great addition to the collection. You can still buy ammo for this gun and shoot it. What a hoot and a lot of fun. It is the first gun designed for the high pressures of the smokeless powder. Of what I understand it hold 8 rounds, so sorry New York, this assault rifle is not for you. I recommend you move back to the United States. Below is the Wiki about it and it's great history. Priced to move @ $500.00

Sorry, I don't have the original box and papers. Gun is in good fireable shape. It has been in the safe for many years only to be pulled and cleaned and inspected. Look at my other ads also. I will be selling the bulk of my collection over the next month or so to fund a large project. I will have some things for sale that will interest all different collectors and shooters.

Sorry, I prefer not to ship. I don't have the time or schedule to accomodate. Thus the discounted local price.

The Lebel Model 1886 rifle (French: Fusil Modèle 1886 dit "Fusil Lebel") is also known as the "Fusil Mle 1886 M93", after a bolt modification was added in 1893. It is an 8mm bolt action infantry rifle which entered service in the French Army in April 1887. It is a repeating rifle that can hold eight rounds in its forestock tube magazine plus one round in the transporter. The Lebel rifle had the distinction of being the first military firearm to use smokeless powder ammunition. The new gunpowder, "Poudre B", was nitrocellulose-based and had been invented in 1884 by French chemist Paul Vieille. . Lt. Colonel Nicolas Lebel contributed the flat nosed 8mm full metal jacket bullet ("Balle M", or "Balle Lebel"). The first practical full metal jacket rifle bullets had just been invented in 1881 by a Lt. Colonel (then Captain) Eduard Rubin (Swiss Army). Somewhat later, in 1898, a ballistically superior pointed (spitzer) AND boat-tail bullet was adopted for the Lebel rifle. It was made of solid brass and called "Balle D". Featuring an oversized bolt with front locking lugs and a massive receiver, the Lebel rifle was a durable design capable of effective long range performance with " Balle D " . In spite of outdated features, such as its tube magazine and the sharply tapered case of 8mm Lebel ammunition, the Lebel rifle remained the basic weapon of French infantry during World War I (1914–18).

title: For Sale:  5.56 Daewoo DR200
postcontent:
The K2 rifles were designed as improved variations of the M16 rifle. While retaining most of the  M16 design features, Daewoo designers replaced the direct gas system of the AR-15/M16 rifle with the more common and reliable gas piston system, and made several other improvements, resulting in very good combat weapon.

 The following parts in the DR-200 are common with the AR15 series: hammer, disconnector, trigger, hammer spring, disconnector spring, firing pin retainer (cotter pin), bolt cam pin, magazines, hammer and trigger pins, flash hider on pre-ban [AR100], front sling swivel, rear sight drum and detent same as m16a1, front take down pivot pin and detent. Converting to pre-ban config is easy due to this. Since it uses a gas piston and regulator, not direct impingement, cleaning is easy and operation is nominally flawless.

title: For Sale/Trade:  SAFE Act Non-compliance
postcontent:
As of March 15, an NCIC check must be completed by a licensed firearms dealer for all private sales of guns.  However, unlike the federal rules for an NCIC background check, which require the record to be destroyed after 24 hours, the SAFE act requires that dealers MUST MAINTAIN A RECORD OF PRIVATE SALE BACKGROUND CHECKS.  Essentially, this establishes a gun registry as dealers will at some point be required to submit records of private sale background checks to the state.
If you owned your gun before March 15, 2013 there is absolutely no reason to submit to the required NCIC background check when selling it since there is no way for the state to know when it might have been sold.
